A quick stop off at the park and kiosk
Aug 2022 • Family
I was on a European cruise August 22 with my partner, his sister and her family and our third stop was Lisbon. We explored some of the area and after quite a bit of a walk found this nice little park, it was such hot day but it wasn’t too busy. There’s a cafe that we didn’t use but we did sit and order from the small kiosk. Coffee was ok but could’ve been better but we got some lovely Portuguese egg custards. There’s a small play area of a climbing frame, benches, a lake and also public toilets. Lots of bird life about the place. A nice little park.
Written July 30, 2023

Nice park with lots of benches
Apr 2023 • Couples
Our first day in Lisbon we just walked the streets and found this nice park known also as Jardim Guerra Junqueiro full of trees, flowers, benches and lots of relaxing people but not overcrowded. There are several entries - from Praca da Estrela just opposite the church, from Ave Alvares Cabral, from Rua da Estrela and from Rua de Sao Bernardo. We spent there about hour just enjoying the walk through it. There ae also some cafes, public toilets etc.

Lovely little park
Apr 2022 • Couples
This lovely park is on the tram 28 route...we spotted it on the way to the end/start of the route. It looked lovely from the outside so we hopped off and had a wander around. It was packed full of local families enjoying a sunny Sunday afternoon. There are a couple of cafés to stop at and watch locals enjoying life, and a large variety of trees and plants for those interested.

If you fancy a bit of green when in Lisbon, head up here.
Written May 15, 2022
